Here's how to implement all three parts:

**1 & 2. Intercept back navigation with a confirmation dialog**

Override `OnBackButtonPressed` in your page:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (!_hasUnsavedChanges)
            return base.OnBackButtonPressed();

        // Fire-and-forget the async dialog; return true to cancel navigation
        Dispatcher.Dispatch(async () =>
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (leave)
            {
                _hasUnsavedChanges = false;
                await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
            }
        });

        return true; // true = cancel the default back navigation
    }
}
```

> **Note:** `OnBackButtonPressed` only fires for the **hardware/OS back button** (Android back gesture, etc.). It does **not** fire when the user taps Shell's navigation bar back arrow.

**3. Custom "Cancel" back button in the nav bar**

Replace Shell's default back arrow with a toolbar item:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{x:Null}">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior
            TextOverride="Cancel"
            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}"
            IconOverride="" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

Then in your view model (or code-behind):

```csharp
public ICommand CancelCommand { get; }

public EditProductPageViewModel()
{
    CancelCommand = new AsyncRelayCommand(OnCancelAsync);
}

private async Task OnCancelAsync()
{
    if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!leave) return;
    }

    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

**Key points:**

- `Shell.BackButtonBehavior` controls the **nav bar** back button (text, icon, command).
- `OnBackButtonPressed()` controls the **hardware/OS** back button — return `true` to cancel.
- You need **both** to fully guard against unsaved-changes navigation.
